    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="374"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d374">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/15408½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">2 July, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: It seems to me that the
                    importance of attempting a settlement in Mexico grows daily more pressing, and
                    that you would therefore be justified in asking these gentlemen to come to
                    Washington to confer with you, one by one or in groups, as you think wisest.
                    They will be complimented, I am sure, and will enter into the spirit of the
                    thing.</p>
                <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. W.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
